commitResults.message: Added the ability to store the text entered by the user in the order of input and display them back to the user when requested using the keyword: list.
Able to add tasks to the list, retrieve the list using keyword:list and mark tasks as done.

Did Level 4, The naming convention has yet to be changed/standardized as priority is to get the working/accurate code up before the stipulated deadlin! working well with some minor user_input problem handling will be improving this at Level 5

Level 5 completed! Made a lot more error handling features and added the extension which was to do exceptions to handle the errors as suggested. Handles most errors pretty well and also has an additional duke-manual feature which is to aid the user in knowing what exactly to type to do what as just saying their input was wrong did not seem sufficient. Also throws useful descriptions for the different errors and explains what is missing!
Completed Level 7, able to store the list to persistent memory using serial files. Saving happens upon any change to the task list and the list is automatically imported upon launch of Duke!

Level-8 is now complete, Now Duke knows the date and time entered by the user than simply just storing it as a string did some standardization minor bug fixes such as cutting unneccessary portions. Duke also has a manual!!
Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
Give users a way to find a task by searching for a keyword.
Used the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate testing of Duke.
